storyInfo: The Duke of Windermere is attacked by the Sanguinarch of Vampires, Confessarius and Damazti on the battleship that the Rhodes Island personnel are on. The Sanguinarch of Vampires kills the Duke of Windermere.

attributes.text: Endless reports.
An avalanche of intel has flooded this lonely battleship ever since it left Norport.
\nThere are signs of trouble from Leithanien to the east, Sargon to the southwest, Kjerag to the west... while everything remains silent in the south.
The messages are suffocating, eating away at my nerves.
My mother seems utterly unmoved, impassively issuing order after order.
\nBut even she cannot resist a frown when she reads the 'congratulations' from her fellow dukes.
This is her life.
\nShe is here, and so this is my Lynncardine.
\nI am home.
Focus, Delphine. Listen to the reports. This is no time to let your mind wander.
She adjusts the position of her eye patch. Is it to hide the wrinkles?
\nThe weather here is very different from Lynncardine. It's suppressed, heavy, the gloom of rain and fog ever present.
\nI just want to—

attributes.content: What are you gazing at so absent-mindedly, Delphine?
Nothing, Mother.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: It's just...
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: I don't get to see Londinium from this angle very often.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: I know how you look when your mind is wandering.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Are you bored by the chatters from the rear?
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: No... I'm just thinking about Norport Borough.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Sorry, I didn't expect the situation in Londinium to deteriorate so much, so quickly.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: I should have arranged for your evacuation sooner.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: We had compiled reports on everything that went on in Londinium, but we weren't able to bring them.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: We should be the ones apologizing.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: That's alright. A few little troubles don't mean much to the big picture.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Perhaps the Duke of Caster should be held responsible for most of them.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: I know. Let's hope my Messenger isn't making things too difficult for her right now.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: But the value of that intel to subsequent operations...
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Pales in comparison to your value, Delphine. Relax.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: I'm here, and Irnclad Galavae is nearby. Everything will be right again once we return to the city.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: We'll restore Londinium, and Victoria.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Of course.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Mother, I...
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: I thought I would die down there.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: I wouldn't let that happen to my daughter.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: You've done well. You have the patience and attention to detail of your father.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: But you don't have to be the one to do all that work. You're my heir, and your place is at Lynncardine.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Our standoff with Leithanien can be trying. You'll need to get used to those matters. Plus... I could use someone to talk to.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: I thought I could do better.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: ...Sorry.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: There are many things that a Duke of Windermere must worry about, for which she needs nerves of steel.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: But that's not your burden. Not yet.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: You can rely on your mother, at least until she's too old to walk.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: I understand... thank you, mother.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: We'll be home in another four or five hours. I've arranged for all the stuff you left behind at the old house to be set up.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Your pajamas, your pillow, your bed, your bathtub.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: That's all stuff from before I came to Londinium—
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: It's not like you're any taller.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: I have some nice things for you as well, but I'll keep those a secret for now.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Get a good night's sleep once we're back.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: But don't get complacent. We have a lot to do.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: What is it?
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: I was in Londinium a long time, wasn't I?
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: I had many friends. Outstanding friends, from whom I had a lot to learn.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: We lived in a city in disorder, chewing up and swallowing the lives we once had. But we believed in our cause. I was proud of it.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Then... things changed. One agent after another disappeared, and the Sarkaz took the city...
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: I was on my own. I had to live with more... common people. For the first time, I learned how they lived, and how they viewed Victoria.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Most of them are dead now. Those who still live huddle in the bowels of this ship, waiting for you to decide their fate.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: One hundred meters beneath my pajamas, bed, and bathtub.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Hmm.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: I'm really grateful, really, but is it all because—
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.text: She does not let me finish.
\nShe puts her hand on my head without patting it, but I know this is her way of showing affection.

attributes.content: You did well, my daughter. You exceeded my expectations.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Go and see the troops below. It'll do you good to talk with them.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.text: With that, Her Grace departs. She's always swift and decisive. I have no chance to say any more.
\nI scratch my slightly untidy head.

attributes.content: Mother!
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: We can talk later.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: You shouldn't have come here yourself!
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.text: The words that come out of my own mouth surprise me.
\nWas it not because of my call for help that she came?
\nHow could I say that.

attributes.content: It's too... risky!
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: We can't fully trust the Leithanians, and we don't know what the Sarkaz are planning next!
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: We've fallen behind on intel—
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.text: She dismisses me with a wave, perhaps telling me not to think too much about it.
\nHer silhouette remains sharp, making me feel like I'm worrying too much, and that she can take handle it all.
Sigh. She's right.
\nI'm not much taller at all.

attributes.content: How long will our food last?
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: I don't think this warship was prepared to take on so many refugees.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: We can't just leave 'em to fend for themselves!
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: Mrs. Emil grabbed my hand just now. She didn't say nuffin'. All she did was look at me...
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: I... I can't take it anymore. Let's find Delphine!
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: Calm down, Hannah. We're on someone else's ship.
attributes.name: Dagda

attributes.content: I just—
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: I'll go keep 'em company. The old timers will feel better with a familiar face around.
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: I'll stay with you.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: Sorry to keep you waiting. I talked to the quartermaster.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Some food will make it to those who need it most... that's the best I can do.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Thank you, Delphine, and thanks to Duke Windermere.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: Part of me hopes that Mother really wants to help these poor people out of the kindness of her heart, but...
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: I know. It's because of me, or should I say, because of who I am.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: It's fine, as long as it helps the people who fled with us.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: You've adapted quickly, Vina.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: The time when we could do as we pleased has passed, Delphine.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: Many souls on this ship are counting on me. I have a responsibility to them, both as Vina and as the Siege.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.text: Lots of people are looking at us. I can tell Vina is busy.
Mother's ship is one of the biggest of the Victorian ships-of-the-line, but it was never designed to evacuate civilians. Certainly not this many.
\nThe people of Norport are squeezed into holds meant to store ammunition and weapons, trying their best to find a clean place to sit down.
\nThis is not the best accommodation, even if the most dangerous weapons have been removed. Vina's gang are doing their best to maintain order.
\nThe refugees whisper about her amongst themselves. The officers on the ship pay no heed, nor does Vina respond to their calls of 'Your Majesty' or 'Your Royal Highness'.
Regardless, she has become the heart and soul of this place.

\nPerhaps the civilians don't even realize themselves, but the reason they trust Vina is not so much because of her status, but because she is the only one they can rely on in this unfamiliar environment.

attributes.content: How goes the war?
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: The number of reports coming in is unreal. Too many variables to keep track of.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: The Duke of Wellington's offensive is unsteady, and our own defensive lines are being pressed...
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: We should have an overwhelming advantage in terms of forces, even if the dukes have yet to commit their full strength. We are facing a foe beyond the scope of modern military theory.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: The Nachzehrer King... the only thing we know about him comes from sparse records of ancient times.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: It has been too long since Victoria, indeed Terra as a whole, last faced a real Sarkaz army.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: What chain reaction will their witchcraft produce? Are they really as primitive and backwards as the records say?
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: What force have the various Sarkaz branches come together to form, where we can't see them? Why do they stand together?
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: No need to worry too much, though. Mother... Duke Windermere and Duke Wellington will conduct this war together.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: The Duke of Caster has also publicly declared her allegiance. The stalemate will not last long.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Once we return to Irnclad Galavae, both supplies and support will—
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Whoa! What was that?
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: Looks like we're passing through a canyon... a good thing. It means we're about to leave the battlefield.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.text: A canyon.
\nI feel even less at ease.
\nI know where mother's confidence comes from. This ship is defended by Windermere's pride, her Swordguards.
\nIf the Sarkaz think this merely a reckless act by the Duke of Windermere, they will find themselves on the receiving end of blades that have been honed since the War of the Four Emperors.
But do we truly know the Sarkaz?

attributes.content: Is the ship slowing down, Siege?
attributes.name: Dagda

attributes.content: I think so. And the weather outside... say, what time is it?
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: How long has it been since we left Norport?
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: A few hours, I think.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Is this just an ordinary canyon?
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: Yes, nothing remarkable besides some abandoned factories...
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.text: Abandoned factories. Yes, this place has been abandoned since before Londinium fell into chaos.
\nWhy? Because of Catastrophe.
\nThe massive crystal formations that Catastrophe left behind...

attributes.content: Be careful!
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: Hey, I'm talking to you!
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.text: Something's not right.
\nThere's a different smell in the air.
I look around instinctively. All the elite soldiers in the hold are gone.
This is not right!

attributes.content: Get away from him, Hannah!
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.text: Siege pulls her back before I can.
\nI see the soldier smiling at me.

attributes.content: Look out!
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.text: It's too late.
Blood seeps from the gaps in the ceiling, dripping into the infiltrator's eyes.
\nDrip.
\nMerge.
\nSpread.
Blood?
\nWhere did this blood come from?

attributes.content: Look out!
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.text: Siege pushes me away. An instant later, a blood mist bursts where I stood.
\nSoon, the entire hold is engulfed in crimson.

attributes.content: Blood mist? Sarkaz witchcraft!
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Too many civilians here.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: Morgan, Dagda, Indra.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.text: The four of them exchange gazes, and take up positions around the frightened crowd.
\nThe emotions in the crowd ranges from shock to panic. Some in the corners begin to scream, without even seeing exactly what happened.

attributes.content: Go down! The stairs are to the north!
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Lady Delphine!
attributes.name: Shearer

attributes.content: Are you the ship's doctor?
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: We're under attack by witchcraft. The ship's casters can't decipher it yet. The Duke and—
attributes.name: Shearer

attributes.content: Damn, how did they—
attributes.name: Shearer

attributes.content: Look out!
attributes.name: Dagda

attributes.text: A claw slaps away the sword that was inches from his throat.
\nThe blood mist disperses, then reconverges, taking a gooey, wet form.
A Sarkaz emerges from the bloody shadow.

attributes.content: (In Sarkaz) The Vampire's witchcraft has taken hold.
attributes.name: Confessarius Guard

attributes.content: I know that outfit... the skull mask...
attributes.name: Dagda

attributes.content: (In Sarkaz) The Sighs of Kings... one variable to eliminate.
attributes.name: Confessarius Guard

attributes.content: (In Sarkaz) Cause chaos and eliminate the outblood. Hesitate not to spill your own blood.
attributes.name: Confessarius Guard

attributes.content: (In Sarkaz) Oh?
attributes.name: Confessarius Guard

attributes.content: You were part of the siege of the Knights of the Tower...
attributes.name: Dagda

attributes.content: Careful! I've gotcha!
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: (In Sarkaz) You will die here with your king, Victorian.
attributes.name: Confessarius Guard

attributes.content: (In Sarkaz) Do it.
attributes.name: Confessarius Guard

attributes.content: (Mother is on deck, but we still have civilians and our people below... I...)
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Delphine! Your left!
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: Ugh!
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Careful.
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: Sorry, thanks.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: There aren't many of them. We can pin them down. The reinforced compartment is one bulkhead away. Get the civilians there—
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: No, there's something more important that you must do.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: Those people came with me. I promised to protect them.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: Duke Windermere likely doesn't know how bad things are below.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: Go and inform her. I'll hold out until your reinforcements arrive.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: But I—
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: This suits us better. You have a formal command structure. There's no way to integrate us quickly.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: Vina...
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Go!
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: Damn, you've got a hard head. Almost made my hand go numb.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: *Sarkaz profanity*...
attributes.name: Confessarius Guard

attributes.content: (In Sarkaz) So be it. The Sighs of Kings will be spoils enough.
attributes.name: Confessarius Guard

attributes.content: (In Sarkaz) Surround the Aslan.
attributes.name: Confessarius Guard

attributes.content: Get ready for a brawl, mates.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.text: For an instant, I wished I was with them.
\nLike when I first joined Slobberknocker Gym, when I went from being alone to being in a community.
\nCador, and... Baird.
\nWe stood together.

attributes.content: This ends now.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.text: The swing of the hammer compresses the air in the passage. It roars.
\nTiny drops of liquid fall on my face.
\nMy vision blurs.

attributes.content: Delphine!

attributes.text: A shadow draws near.

attributes.content: Delphine!
Mother?
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.text: I try to wipe my eyes.
\nI see another pair of eyes right there in front of me.
\nRed flows from their sockets.

attributes.content: Delphine... go no further...
attributes.name: Victorian Officer

attributes.content: You're hurt—
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: You'll only be in the way. Same for me.
attributes.name: Victorian Officer

attributes.content: Kill me, before whatever this is consumes me.
attributes.name: Victorian Officer

attributes.content: The Swordguards and Her Grace will kill the Sarkaz.
attributes.name: Victorian Officer

attributes.content: Do not put yourself in danger, Delphine... no...
attributes.name: Victorian Officer

attributes.content: I don't even feel the pain anymore...
attributes.name: Victorian Officer

attributes.content: Free me. Then stop.
attributes.name: Victorian Officer

attributes.text: I draw my sword.
\nShe is still conscious. I should not do this to her. But I see the relief in her eyes.
\nShe grabs my sword, sending it into her own body.
\nI'm trembling. I can't see clearly.

attributes.content: Lady Delphine—You must live—
attributes.name: Victorian Officer

attributes.content: Thank you—for freeing me—
attributes.name: Victorian Officer

attributes.text: I look down and see the red eyes.
\nShe gives up breathing, smiling to the end.

attributes.content: This is... Sarkaz...
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Mother...
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.text: My feet cannot move. Worry, unease, and fear grip them.
\nThe lights go out. The only light comes from above deck.
There is only silence amongst the bodies. Rain solidifies as it falls.
\nFlowing backwards, evaporating, converging.
\nA red-black sun rises into the sky, obscuring its white counterpart.
A bloodless complexion emerges from the black sun, not a speck of blood on it.
\nHe descends from the black sun.
I avert my gaze.
Am I afraid?
\nHow shameful...

attributes.content: Hmm.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: You should not have dodged.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: The paleness of your face would have contrasted well with the blood drops.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: They would have painted a picture of beautiful despair.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: Hmph.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Leeches can't stop playing with blood, I see.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Nothing has changed with you people, even after all these centuries.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.text: Rain begins to fall again.
\nDrip. Drop.

attributes.content: Look.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: It's a good day to die.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: Your Grace, this attack was planned.
attributes.name: Swordguard

attributes.content: As expected.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: For a sovereign of the Sarkaz to pay a personal visit, though... all well and good, I suppose.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: The battle below is not going well. The officers are organizing the defense.
attributes.name: Swordguard

attributes.content: No matter. This one is our only threat.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.text: Mother... the Duke of Windermere points her sword towards the invading Sarkaz leader.
\nI cannot see the expression on her face, but I know that is not the mother I know so well.
\nThe soldier was right. I would only be in the way.

attributes.content: I've long had enough of Leithanian Spire Arts.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: I wonder what the spine of a Vampire looks like.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Hmmm.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: You're a strong Victorian. You don't think you'll shirk back.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: But your blood will betray you.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: The creator built a bridge of life for humanity, and I stand above the bridge.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: Oh?
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: Not any worse than those spire madmen.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.text: A blue blade cuts through the rain of blood.
\nA tiny drop of rain cuts open Mother's cheek.
\nWas it the red rain, or blood seeping out? I could not see.
\nThere is no change in Mother's expression, but... have I ever seen her get hurt before?

attributes.content: Poor fool.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: Still clinging to dreams and fantasies.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: Guess why your battleship fell from within?
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: Focus on the mission at hand, soldiers.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Ready.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Roger.
attributes.name: Swordguard

attributes.content: Your duty is to kill the enemies of Windermere, not protect the life of Windermere.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Do all you can to weaken the Sarkaz. Victoria will take back what is hers.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.text: The Vampire's movement starts to slow.
\nNo, the Swordguards are too fast.
I've received formal military training. I did not go to Londinium unprepared.
\nBut here and now, I realize the weight of the words 'Duke of Windermere'.
\nMy mother never let her daughter see the kinds of battlefields that she knew.

attributes.content: Hm.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: Not bad, not bad... you aren't a duke of Victoria for nothing.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: How many Sarkaz have you eaten?
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: I don't have any such disgusting habits.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: No.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: You and your ancestors reveled in war, from Kazimierz to Leithanien.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: A Duke of Windermere once had an army of Sarkaz. In the War of the Four Nations, which engulfed most of the land...
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: How did you or your ancestor use them?
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: Parlor tricks, the theft of witchcraft, a favorite of the Nachzehrer.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: The blood and flesh of Sarkaz spread across the battlefield, becoming yet another bulwark for your glorious armada.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: You ate them up, alright.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: Are you after revenge, Sarkaz?
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Of course.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: How dare you trifle with the methods of my creation, the property of the Crimson Court?
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: He's being strengthened by the blood of the fallen?
attributes.name: Swordguard

attributes.content: No.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: It is no longer bodily fluids, but a part of the curse.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Prepare counter-Arts.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.text: Stay calm.
\nTake a deep breath.
My throat is coarse. I cannot speak. I try to gasp for air, but the smell of blood is all there is.
Vampire and... Confessarius.
\nThis is Mother's flagship. Lynncardine's most experienced commanders, bravest sailors and most steadfast warriors are gathered here.
\nMother once told me that war is not about heroes, about charging into danger. A commander must see the whole battlefield, in order to see the way to victory.
But—
\nI realize why this ship sailed deep behind enemy lines without support.
Because of me.
No...
\nThis is no time for self-flagellation.
\nI have to do something. If there is no place on Mother's battlefield for me... someone must bring order.
One of the Kings of the Sarkaz Court is here. But would they really attack us so recklessly?
\nMy espionage background tells me that something is missing from this puzzle.
\nI have to do something.
Think!

attributes.content: Could it be...? No, Arts that can teleport an entire army are unheard of... our ship fell from within...
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: I know this feeling...
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.text: Damazti.
\nI encountered him personally when leaving Norport. I had heard about this terrible King of the Sarkaz Court from Amiya. But he was defeated. How could he...?
\nStill, this is the most likely answer.
There are two Kings of the Sarkaz Court on this ship.
\nA truly terrifying conclusion.

attributes.content: But what about the Vampire? Why didn't he go straight to his target, if he could use his witchcraft on the officers?
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Attacking secondary targets with witchcraft, then creating disorder with assassins... that's too inefficient.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: But the Sarkaz fighting with Mother...
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: The Damazti... did he simply infiltrate us by taking the face of a Victorian?
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: If...
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: —Damn it!
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Mother!
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Delphine?! Stay back—
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: That one's fake!
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.text: The Swordguards' weapons impale the Vampire.
\nThe light of Arts penetrate the Sarkaz's twisted visage. The Arts of the Swordguards of Windermere, passed down from generation to generation, are simple, but brutally effective.
Mother quickly sets her sights back on the target.
\nI draw my sword.
\nThe Swordguards do not hear my cry, but Mother is ready.
The Vampire laughs.
\nThe massive Blood Arts explode before it can be cast.
A gust of wind sweeps through the sticky air, blowing away the sanguine rain and wind.
\nDeath falls silent. True terror begins to spread, slowly but surely.
\nBlood converges upon the hand of the silhouette, forming a crystal. Then...
The other, the true—

attributes.content: Enough.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: I don't enjoy seeing another wear my face.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.text: The Swordguards pull back instantly.
\nEven so, two of them are late by an eyelash, and their flesh takes incomprehensible form in a split second.
\nI can feel my sword hand trembling, my throat seizing up. This is a battle beyond my comprehension.

attributes.content: A little girl saw through your disguise.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: You're losing your touch, Damazti. The previous you would have been more convincing.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: Is that so?
attributes.name: Damazti Cluster

attributes.content: These Arts are merely a poor imitation by the Confessarius.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: Foul, uncouth, vulgar killing.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.text: He looks towards me, then towards Mother.
\nI'm trembling.

attributes.content: Delphine.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Y-Yes!
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Good job seeing through the trick. All the Swordguards would have been lost.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: But there's nothing more you can do here now.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: I, I—
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: The escort fleet is approaching. We must ensure that communication with the fleet is maintained.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: The communications tower... it's behind the deck!
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: The enemy is few in number. Go.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: ...I'm counting on you.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.text: She pats my shoulder with an injured hand.
\nOnly then do I notice that she has many more scars on her than I remembered.

attributes.content: Understood.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.text: I turn around and run for the communications tower.
\nPride overcame fear in that instant. Mother said, 'I'm counting on you.'
I see the Confessarii trying to blow the communications tower, and our soldiers still resisting.

attributes.content: Thank goodness, the communications tower hasn't fallen yet—
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: The ship's slowing down?
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: It's the engines! They're attacking the engine room!
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: D-Damn it!
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: Grab my hand!
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Don't look back! Get up!
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Thank you! Oh, L-Lady Delphine—
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: We must regroup and counterattack. Reinforcements are on the way.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Listen up, men!
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Dust clouds in the distance! Help is on the way!
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Their plan—
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.text: Has failed? So easily?
I turn around.
\nThe front of the deck has been completely engulfed in red fog, with only the flashing of sword and vampiric Arts to penetrate it.
Why do I feel so uneasy?
\nI—

attributes.content: Delphine! Look out!
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.text: A pair of eyes peer at me, in the infinite raindrops, in the reflection of blood on the deck.
\nThe Vampire's hand brushes my neck. Why? Is he not fighting Mother?
Vina tries to push me away, but it's too late.
My sword. I still have my sword.
\nI am her daughter.
\nShe is counting on me.
The blood-woven crimson witchcraft vanishes into thin air.

attributes.content: *Pant*... *pant*...
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Are you alright?
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: I'm fine... it's all in my head...
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Your troops are holding back the enemy down below, so we've come up to help.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: The bad news is that we found traces of the Damazti down there.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: We know. The Sanguinarch and Damazti are attacking together.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: No, wait...
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.text: That attack was not a Damazti feint. It was true blue vampiric witchcraft.
\nIf the King of the Sarkaz Court had intended to kill me, there is no reason I should still be alive.
\nIt was not my own strength that allowed me to resist.
\nHe had other plans. There's no doubt about that.
Once again, I look towards the Swordguards. Their swords are still flashing. I can faintly see their silhouettes converging—
Something's not right.
\nThey are falling, one by one.
\nThey're backing up?
This is not right!
\nWhere is Mother?

attributes.content: Delphine? Where are you going?
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: Agh, dreadful!
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: (In Sarkaz) The scent of blood has changed. The Confessarius has succeeded, as has the Sanguinarch.
attributes.name: Confessarius Guard

attributes.content: (In Sarkaz) Pull back.
attributes.name: Confessarius Guard

attributes.content: (In Sarkaz) Those unable to do so, drive your daggers into your hearts on my command.
attributes.name: Confessarius Guard

attributes.content: You—
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.text: Impossible.
\nEven if the fight against the fake Vampire had taken its toll, Mother and her Swordguards could not have fallen so easily.
\nI know the legends of Windermere's sword which no wall could stop, the blade of light that struck down the spires, one of Victoria's two sharpest swords.
\nI grew up listening to them.
Why? How?
I charge into the fog of blood, hearing only my accelerating heartbeat.
\nFinally, I spy a figure.

attributes.content: Ugh...
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: You have lost all sensation in your arms. Your guards are routed.
attributes.name: Damazti Cluster

attributes.content: How do you feel now?
attributes.name: Damazti Cluster

attributes.content: Argh... ugh...
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Sarkaz...
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: He caught you.
attributes.name: Damazti Cluster

attributes.content: An instant of weakness, of disorder... why? We do not understand.
attributes.name: Damazti Cluster

attributes.content: We find it... regrettable.
attributes.name: Damazti Cluster

attributes.content: She's finished. Let this great warrior savor the fading of life.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: Are you leaving?
attributes.name: Damazti Cluster

attributes.content: I have no interest in the inconsequential deaths that remain.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.text: One glance from that devil is enough to freeze my blood.
\nBut he does not kill me.

attributes.content: This blood is a penny a gallon.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: What are you after? We are unsure.
attributes.name: Damazti Cluster

attributes.content: The age of shame is coming to an end.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: Are you hurt?
attributes.name: Damazti Cluster

attributes.content: ...It does not matter.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.text: He disappears into the blood.

attributes.content: Y... You...
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Oh, there you are.
attributes.name: Damazti Cluster

attributes.content: The one who saw through us.
attributes.name: Damazti Cluster

attributes.content: He said we were losing our touch. How convincing was the last one?
attributes.name: Damazti Cluster

attributes.content: Is this good enough?
attributes.name: Damazti Cluster

attributes.content: Don't—you dare—wear her—face—
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.text: He smiles at me with Mother's face.

attributes.content: ...We must try.
attributes.name: Damazti Cluster

attributes.text: Then, with an identical sword—Mother's sword—
\nHe impales his own chest.

attributes.content: Sarkaz!
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.text: In my fury I try to charge, but my body refuses to move.

attributes.content: (In Sarkaz) We'll do better next time.
attributes.name: Damazti Cluster

attributes.text: He whispers in my ear, wearing my own face.
\nMother's sword is still in his chest.
\nIn 'my' chest.
He falls, then familiar blood witchcraft covers him, consuming him.
\nAfter the blood boils and evaporates, it is as though nothing had ever happened.
All I can do is pick up Mother's sword.
I catch sight of Mother.
The sound of fighting has stopped. The wind has calmed. The ship has stopped.
\nI see blue hair on the ground. Mother is bleeding.

attributes.content: Delphine...
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: I can't see very well...
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Have they retreated?
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Mo...ther...
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: They're gone...
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Mother... I, I'll call for the doctors—
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: You'll be fine. You're the Duke of Windermere. You're my mother.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Wait here, I'll—
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: I couldn't beat him... I can't believe it...
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Don't go, Delphine... don't go...
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Let me... look at you...
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.text: Mother's body grows cold in my arms.
\nI dare not let go.
\nThe sound of Mother's heartbeat fades further and further away.

attributes.content: Don't cry.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: I... I'm not crying, Mother.
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: I saw you swing your sword, Delphine... very good.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: You had injured your hand. Your grip... it was never right. I was too hasty.
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Mother... don't say any more...
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.text: Mother gazes towards the horizon. Is that the direction of Londinium?
\nHer eyes have always lain upon Victoria.

attributes.content: I remember... the direction your father left in...
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: We had a surprise for you... one that we prepared long ago...
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Mother...
attributes.name: Delphine

attributes.content: Delphine, you—
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: I thought you would be taller... the clothes will be a bit loose...
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.content: Just... calm down, Delphine...
attributes.name: Duke of Windermere

attributes.text: The rain stops.
